racteristic forenames:  French Michel, Aime, Alphonse, Alphy, Armand, Cecile, Celestine, Emile, Fernand, Germaine, Gilles, Jacques.","English (of Norman origin) and French: from the Old French personal name <i>Bard(e)</i>, ancient Germanic <i>Bardo</i>, from <i>barta</i> ‘battle axe’. This was borne as a surname by a prominent Norman family with lands in west Normandy and in various English and Scottish counties, including Essex, Hertfordshire, North Yorkshire, Northumberland, and Lanarkshire. In Scotland the original family were Norman landowners in Strathaven parish in Lanarkshire. They were descended from the Baards, lords of Loftus in the North Yorkshire, descendants of the mid 12th-century Richard <i>Baart</i>.","Irish: altered form of either   Beard   or   Baird  ."]}]},{"name":"Sir","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Simon  , now rare, but more common in the Middle Ages, when it gave rise to the surnames <i>Simms</i> and <i>Simpson</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Simon","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]},{"name":"Lawrence","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of   Laurence .  This is the usual spelling of the surname, and is now becoming increasingly common as a given name, especially in North America."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Lawrence Baird was born about 1340, in Peeblesshire, Scotland, his father, Thomas de Baird Of Posso Sheriff of Peebles, was 46 and his mother, Lilias Greive, was 28. He married Elizabeth de Somerville. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1364, in his hometown, at the age of 25, and was buried in Peeblesshire, Scotland."},"et":{"about 1340–1364":"umbes 1340–1364","1340–1364":"1340–1364","1340–1384":"1340–1384","1355–1458":"1355–1458","1296–1346":"1296–1346","1313–Female":"1313–Surnud","1458":"1458","1313":"1313","1346":"1346","before 1343":"enne 1343","1355":"1355","1364":"1364","1296":"1296","1384":"1384","1340":"1340","Abt 1346":"umbes 1346","about 1340":"umbes 1340","Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Scotland","England":"England","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1340–1364":"noin 1340–1364","1340–1364":"1340–1364","1340–1384":"1340–1384","1355–1458":"1355–1458","1296–1346":"1296–1346","1313–Female":"1313–Kuollut","1458":"1458","1313":"1313","1346":"1346","before 1343":"ennen vuotta 1343","1355":"1355","1364":"1364","1296":"1296","1384":"1384","1340":"1340","Abt 1346":"noin 1346","about 1340":"noin 1340","Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Scotland","England":"England","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1340–1364":"environ 1340–1364","1340–1364":"1340–1364","1340–1384":"1340–1384","1355–1458":"1355–1458","1296–1346":"1296–1346","1313–Female":"1313–Décédée","1458":"1458","1313":"1313","1346":"1346","before 1343":"avant 1343","1355":"1355","1364":"1364","1296":"1296","1384":"1384","1340":"1340","Abt 1346":"environ 1346","about 1340":"environ 1340","Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Valle de Twede, Écosse","England":"Angleterre","Scotland":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Sir Lawrence Baird est né environ 1340, à Valle de Twede, Écosse, son père, Thomas de Baird Of Posso Sheriff of Peebles, avait 46 ans et sa mère, Lilias Greive, avait 28 ans. Il a épousé Elizabeth de Somerville. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1364, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 25 ans, et a été enterré à Valle de Twede, Écosse."},"de":{"about 1340–1364":"um 1340–1364","1340–1364":"1340–1364","1340–1384":"1340–1384","1355–1458":"1355–145